The paper discusses the use of machine learning in optimizing the resource allocation in OFDMA-based LTE networks. This falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of genetic algorithms in the optimization process, which falls under information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes an adaptive scheduling solution, which involves the use of clustering and classification algorithms, falling under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
